title: What is the trend for asthma, diabetes and epilepsy unplanned emergency admissions for the under 19s?
analysis_commentary: The rate of emergency admissions for asthma, diabetes and epilepsy in children and young people has declined from 336 per 100,000 in 2010/11 to 312 per 100,000 in 2011/12; however it increased again to 337 in 2012/13.
data_source: NHS Outcomes Framework, Health and Social Care Information Centre
